HEADWORD: Thick wind
<hw>Thick" wind`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>A defect of
respiration in a horse, that is unassociated with noise in breathing or
with the signs of emphysema.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thick-winded</ent>⟦br⟧
